    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="912"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d912">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.3516/7–1346: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-19T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 19, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1329. If you have not done so please telegraph substance Urtel 2177 July 13 to
                    Dairen. Inform Dept whether permission utilize Soviet military communication
                    facilities applies transmission coded messages.</p>
                <p>For your info if transmission messages through Soviet facilities proves
                    unsatisfactory (repeated Nanking as 483) Dept contemplates asking Navy arrange
                    despatch vessel Dairen three or four times monthly for purpose picking up
                    despatches and delivering instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
